                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 422.11 G93/543.]</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Chargé d’Affaires</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Quito</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-10-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 28, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Foreign Office formally states that arbitrator will be appointed as soon as
                    the name of the American arbitrator is made known. The railway protocol will be
                    submitted to the tribunal.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bingham.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
